# Introduction
sssEmit is a SonSilentSea's subproject, which simplifies the particles emitter generation process.

# Installation
## Downloading sssEmit
sssEmit can be found in the sonsilentsea resources/sssEmit subfolder:
```
git clone https://github.com/sanguinariojoe/sonsilentsea.git
cd sonsilentsea/resources/sssEmit
```
## Installing sssEmit (Linux)
You can execute as root:
```
make install
```
If you want to install it in a different location you can use the PREFIX option.
## Activating the extension in [Blender](http://www.blender.org)
The first time that you launch [Blender](http://www.blender.org) just after the installation of the module it is necessary to activate it:

* Go to **File/User Preferences**
* Select the tab **Addons**
* Mark the supported level **Testing**
* Type in the searching field **particle**
* Activate the extension

![Activating sssEmit](https://github.com/sanguinariojoe/sonsilentsea/blob/wiki/doc/wiki/images/activating_sssEmit.png?raw=true)

